{
  "texts": [
    "However, given that this trend mirrors pure Task Arithmetic (see Fig. 3), this is mostly due to TA, while subspace boosting is not harmful here.",
    "In Table 3, we again quantify these trends by reporting the probability of surpassing the base model and the average relative improvement across merge sizes.",
    "TA + SB consistently transitions from unstable early performance to strong, near-100% success as n increases.",
    "At small merge sizes, success rates remain low-23% at n=2 with an average relative change of -4.52-but they rise steadily to 98% at n=10 and reach 100% at n=12, with corresponding improvements of +0.89 and +1.07.",
    "In contrast, TIES + SB, TSV-Merge, and Iso-C all deteriorate monotonically in both probability and relative improvement as the number of experts grows."
  ]
}